{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_12","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba task-plans/cross-path-unified-management-task-plan.md | sed -n '1,120p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\t# Cross-Path Unified Management Task Plan\n     2\t\n     3\t## Priority\n     4\t\n     5\tPriority 1\n     6\t\n     7\t## Objective\n     8\t\n     9\tManage threads across multiple project roots from one control surface.\n    10\t\n    11\t## Scope\n    12\t\n    13\t- cross-path discovery\n    14\t- path-aware grouping and filtering\n    15\t- board actions across roots\n    16\t- remove the need for one project per VS Code window\n    17\t\n    18\t## Tasks\n    19\t\n    20\t### Task 1 — Path Model\n    21\t\n    22\t- normalize cwd/workspace paths\n    23\t- group threads by root or project identity\n    24\t- make path origin visible but compact\n    25\t\n    26\t### Task 2 — Cross-Path Filtering\n    27\t\n    28\t- filter threads by root, project, and active workspace\n    29\t- keep path-based filtering compatible with topic focus and pins\n    30\t\n    31\t### Task 3 — Cross-Path Board Actions\n    32\t\n    33\t- attach, pin, loop, and Codex visibility controls should work regardless of origin path\n    34\t- ensure board remains one unified workspace surface\n    35\t\n    36\t## Exit Criteria\n    37\t\n    38\t- user can manage multiple work roots from one extension surface\n    39\t- path identity is clear without dominating UI\n    40\t- board actions are path-agnostic from the user's perspective\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
